============================================
Slideshow Background Generator for Gnome 2.x
============================================

Goal:
-----

To be able to select few photos in nautilus,
and easily make slideshow background in gnome.


TODO:
-----

- ask for duration (and transition time?) and background name
- checkboxes: "[v] Add to your backgorunds" and "[v] Set as my background"   
- create DEB with script in /usr/share/nautilus-scripts/
- nautilus extension instead of nautilus-script?
- deb package (PPA?)


Instalation:
------------

install --mode 0755 sbg.py ~/.gnome2/nautilus-scripts/"Set as background"


Usage:
------

1. Open a directory with some pictures in nautilus.
2. Select few pictures (use CTRL).
3. Right Click -> Scripts -> Set as background  

or via commandline:
./sbg.py /path/to/myImages*.jpg


